1
00:00:02,313 --> 00:00:11,375
"Secrets Happened on the Litchi Island"

2
00:00:21,720 --> 00:00:22,560
Hello bro.
Have you arrived?

3
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:24,480
I'll ask Chen Li to pick you up.

4
00:00:24,520 --> 00:00:25,391
I am...

5
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:33,895
Listen to me!

6
00:00:33,920 --> 00:00:35,335
One Le coin is equal to 10 yuan.

7
00:00:35,360 --> 00:00:37,320
Don't rob!

8
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:04,880
Mr. Dandan, take the children slowly.

9
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:09,280
I forgot about my brother.

10
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:21,626
Xiao Zhi!

11
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:33,920
It's okay, I'll buy you a new one.

12
00:01:33,960 --> 00:01:35,040
Let's go!

13
00:01:47,665 --> 00:01:48,853
Then pay for it.

14
00:01:51,210 --> 00:01:52,450
What's it to me?

15
00:01:54,428 --> 00:01:55,988
I was just about to call you

16
00:01:56,210 --> 00:01:58,595
when Chen Li shone a flashlight in my face.

17
00:02:03,699 --> 00:02:04,659
And as my hand slipped,

18
00:02:05,016 --> 00:02:05,920
the phone dropped and got smashed.

19
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,240
Isn't it Chen Li's fault?

20
00:02:08,760 --> 00:02:09,760
Bro.

21
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,920
How long have I been on the phone with you?

22
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:13,695
Your bro has already forgotten about you.

23
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:14,712
Chen Li!

24
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:19,320
Count the thing
about the mobile phone on me.

25
00:02:19,320 --> 00:02:20,579
As for the rest,
you can figure it out by yourselves.

26
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:24,280
Nie Xiaolong!

27
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:26,840
It was you who asked me to come
to summer camp as a teaching assistant.

28
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:28,520
It's really not my idea.

29
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:29,477
Chen Li!

30
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:32,704
Count this on me too.

31
00:02:32,759 --> 00:02:33,520
Drink more?
No.

32
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,566
Those teaching assistants
who came last year can't come

33
00:02:37,591 --> 00:02:38,706
because examinations for schools.

34
00:02:38,731 --> 00:02:40,563
So I thought of Xiao Zhi.

35
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:43,215
Hey, Xiaozhi.

36
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:43,840
Hungry?

37
00:02:44,305 --> 00:02:45,400
Let me make something delicious for you.

38
00:02:45,517 --> 00:02:46,117
Okay.

39
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:49,204
Chen Li!

40
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:52,438
Why don't you usually
try to court my favor?

41
00:02:52,595 --> 00:02:54,680
You don't call me brother either.

42
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,000
Xiaodu Mom.
Don't worry.

43
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:58,070
He gets along well with his classmates.

44
00:02:58,095 --> 00:02:59,175
Do you live with your brother?

45
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:00,200
I don't live with him.
He snores and grinds his teeth
while sleeping.

46
00:03:01,765 --> 00:03:02,680
Nie Xiaozhi!

47
00:03:04,603 --> 00:03:05,403
Hurry up!

48
00:03:14,101 --> 00:03:14,880
Teacher Daxiong.

49
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:15,960
My brother has arrived.

50
00:03:19,820 --> 00:03:21,160
Zhang Chu Mom, don't worry.

51
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:23,000
Teacher Dandan has received him.

52
00:03:35,314 --> 00:03:36,689
It's starting again.

53
00:03:43,998 --> 00:03:45,118
I'm going to check the dormitory.

54
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:03,840
What's up?

55
00:04:04,169 --> 00:04:05,560
I'm applying a facial mask.

56
00:04:05,857 --> 00:04:07,106
My brother is an actor.

57
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,400
So I'm borrowing his mask for a while,
do you need it?

58
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:12,480
No, thank you.

59
00:04:29,094 --> 00:04:30,528
What's his name?

60
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:33,184
Do you remember?

61
00:04:42,559 --> 00:04:43,965
Come in and wash up!

62
00:04:58,450 --> 00:04:59,360
Towel!

63
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:57,348
Nie Xiaozhi, go downstairs
to have breakfast.

64
00:07:20,610 --> 00:07:21,286
Morning.
Morning.

65
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:22,840
Breakfast is ready.
Okay.

66
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:25,640
You won't get lost during the day,
will you?

67
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:27,440
Not sure.

68
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:29,960
Let me go with you.

69
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:35,050
It's mine.

70
00:07:35,075 --> 00:07:36,680
Don't snatch, okay?

71
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,960
Don't snatch!

72
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:38,989
Here's more.
Don't snatch!

73
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:42,840
I'm going crazy.

74
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:49,360
It's too noisy inside.

75
00:07:49,385 --> 00:07:50,411
Eat here.

76
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:55,600
Is one cup enough?
That's enough!

77
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,000
Don't want this.

78
00:08:12,997 --> 00:08:14,560
Don't you like children?

79
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:17,000
I don't like them, too noisy.

80
00:08:17,310 --> 00:08:18,567
I like mature ones.

81
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:22,450
Then you should have an older brother
instead of a younger brother.

82
00:08:23,050 --> 00:08:24,850
Teacher Yue, do you need my help?

83
00:08:24,875 --> 00:08:26,235
Take a hike!

84
00:08:30,753 --> 00:08:32,872
Is Xiaozhi your biological younger brother?

85
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:35,000
Yes, but I always suspect that
he was piked up by my mother.

86
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:35,920
My mom doesn't admit it.

87
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:38,739
He's much better-behaved than you.

88
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:40,280
Really?

89
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:48,887
Xiaozhi, go and help pick
some wax apples back later.

90
00:08:49,185 --> 00:08:50,146
Okay.

91
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,520
I'll go with you.

92
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:55,575
Oh.

93
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:11,720
It has no taste when eaten directly.

94
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,160
Wait for me to make
licorice wax apples for you.

95
00:09:16,786 --> 00:09:17,720
Chen Li.

96
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,200
Do you think my brother
hasn't been quite right recently?

97
00:09:20,396 --> 00:09:21,156
It's a bit off.

98
00:09:22,442 --> 00:09:24,482
Is Teacher Yue from your school?

99
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:27,960
No, she is Teacher
Ziqin's teaching assistant.

100
00:09:30,458 --> 00:09:31,938
She seems older than my brother.

101
00:09:32,803 --> 00:09:33,563
Exactly.

102
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:36,942
It really seems that my bro
likes elder brothers and sisters.

103
00:09:38,305 --> 00:09:39,105
Elder brother?

104
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,680
I mean to say

105
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:43,920
my brother likes to get along
with older people.

106
00:09:44,169 --> 00:09:45,889
That's why he doesn't like me.

107
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:48,840
The wax apple?

108
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,000
Here it is.

109
00:09:57,552 --> 00:09:58,403
Let me do it.

110
00:10:02,950 --> 00:10:03,841
Let's go.

111
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:11,075
Whoever grabs it again
will have Le coins deducted!

112
00:10:12,265 --> 00:10:13,434
Is it right this time?

113
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:18,872
Kids, come here to get your name tags.

114
00:10:27,766 --> 00:10:29,864
Wait. I'm going to
show off my cooking skills.

115
00:10:36,792 --> 00:10:38,455
Xiaozhi, which school did you graduate from?

116
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:39,240
Primary School No.1.

117
00:10:39,489 --> 00:10:41,200
Xiaozhi is from the same school as me.

118
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:41,960
You too?
Right!

119
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:48,286
Children, come and get the Le coins.

120
00:10:59,875 --> 00:11:00,840
Let me apply it for you.

121
00:11:08,661 --> 00:11:09,638
Here?

122
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,310
Is anywhere else itchy?

123
00:11:29,012 --> 00:11:30,480
Tom for the Group three and group four.

124
00:11:32,036 --> 00:11:33,160
Get ready to start!

125
00:11:33,286 --> 00:11:34,080
Get ready!

126
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:36,440
The large-scale hide-and-seek
competition on Litchi Island starts now!

127
00:11:36,465 --> 00:11:37,665
Start!

128
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,160
Hurry up!

129
00:11:43,856 --> 00:11:45,161
Xiaozhi, I'm nervous.

130
00:11:45,186 --> 00:11:47,270
We should hide separately
and not stay together.

131
00:12:24,333 --> 00:12:25,864
Don't catch me!

132
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:29,036
I got one!

133
00:12:47,489 --> 00:12:49,106
It's raining, let's go!

134
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:55,280
Let me.

135
00:12:58,958 --> 00:12:59,680
Come on.

136
00:13:14,270 --> 00:13:15,280
The weather!

137
00:13:24,407 --> 00:13:26,527
We can't stop it, let's run!

138
00:13:27,044 --> 00:13:28,497
I'll still get soaked
even if we run over there.

139
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:29,887
Come on.

140
00:13:40,977 --> 00:13:43,825
Chen Li, who are you trying to seduce
with your swimming trunks on?

141
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:44,680
Scram!

142
00:13:56,714 --> 00:13:58,403
Hurry up! Don't let my younger brother
catch a cold.

143
00:14:02,363 --> 00:14:03,203
Take a seat!

144
00:14:09,960 --> 00:14:12,130
Xiaozhi, girls would do that.

145
00:14:28,186 --> 00:14:30,512
- Nie Xiaolong!
- Bro!

146
00:14:34,130 --> 00:14:35,942
The sound was right here just now.

147
00:14:38,989 --> 00:14:40,080
Are you afraid of the dark?

148
00:14:40,105 --> 00:14:41,075
A little bit.

149
00:14:41,184 --> 00:14:42,161
Let's go.

150
00:14:45,107 --> 00:14:46,147
Why are we hiding?

151
00:14:46,242 --> 00:14:48,044
If we don't hide now,
we won't be able to explain it clearly.

152
00:14:50,325 --> 00:14:51,403
Go.

153
00:14:56,622 --> 00:14:57,833
Play pranks on them.

154
00:15:10,538 --> 00:15:12,090
It seems that it's going to rain.

155
00:15:12,442 --> 00:15:13,536
Shall we go back?

156
00:15:27,321 --> 00:15:29,364
Where have you been?

157
00:15:30,919 --> 00:15:32,520
I went out for a stroll.

158
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:33,680
Just met Xiaolong.

159
00:15:34,378 --> 00:15:36,338
Took a stroll together, right?

160
00:15:39,097 --> 00:15:40,377
I'm going back first.

161
00:15:40,403 --> 00:15:41,302
Hey.

162
00:15:47,622 --> 00:15:48,440
Did you record it?
Yeah!

163
00:15:52,028 --> 00:15:52,965
Send me.

164
00:16:00,490 --> 00:16:02,340
I just felt that there was
something wrong with him.

165
00:16:29,707 --> 00:16:30,507
Xiaozhi!

166
00:16:34,218 --> 00:16:35,018
Xiaozhi!

167
00:17:46,840 --> 00:17:48,480
The lychee trees hardly bore
any fruit this year.

168
00:17:49,372 --> 00:17:49,975
Mmm.

169
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:52,606
The island owner said that
the trees didn't bloom in spring.

170
00:18:19,770 --> 00:18:20,680
Let me.

171
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:21,920
Let me, let me look for it.

172
00:18:34,333 --> 00:18:35,240
Is there any?

173
00:18:36,680 --> 00:18:37,606
Let me see.

174
00:18:38,569 --> 00:18:39,957
There isn't even a single lychee.

175
00:18:56,864 --> 00:18:58,067
Really not.

176
00:18:59,395 --> 00:19:01,596
People who have never eaten
freshly picked lychees

177
00:19:01,621 --> 00:19:03,309
really can't understand
how delicious they are.

178
00:19:03,426 --> 00:19:04,720
Then shall we check another tree?

179
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:05,544
Let's go!

180
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:26,833
Look at this.

181
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:31,333
Twins?

182
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:33,942
Don't eat it.

183
00:19:36,731 --> 00:19:37,491
No!

184
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:45,480
I only eat freshly picked ones.

185
00:20:12,402 --> 00:20:13,162
One!

186
00:20:27,364 --> 00:20:28,364
For you.

187
00:20:30,107 --> 00:20:30,966
Cheers.

188
00:21:55,760 --> 00:21:56,920
David Hockney?

189
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,040
You know?

190
00:21:59,800 --> 00:22:00,760
I've seen some.

191
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:04,320
His painting style is very vivid.

192
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:07,800
The most famous one is the swimming pool.

193
00:22:08,801 --> 00:22:10,335
He painted a lot of swimming pools.

194
00:22:10,360 --> 00:22:11,680
I can't describe his paintings.

195
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:13,960
Brilliant, vivid, enthusiastic.

196
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:17,606
No matter what words are used to describe
his paintings, they are not accurate.

197
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:47,489
There's no need to pursue accuracy.

198
00:22:48,010 --> 00:22:49,410
Nor should you mind inaccuracy.

199
00:22:50,482 --> 00:22:52,682
Nature endows us
with the diversity of genes.

200
00:22:53,320 --> 00:22:56,840
We should respect these diverse
and uncertain factors.

201
00:22:57,817 --> 00:23:00,177
For example, every time I enter the water

202
00:23:00,202 --> 00:23:01,653
I'm not sure how much splash will be made.

203
00:23:02,505 --> 00:23:03,848
It's also beyond my control.

204
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:05,206
But it can be captured.

205
00:23:05,231 --> 00:23:06,680
The moment you draw it

206
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:08,080
whether it's accurate or not,

207
00:23:08,080 --> 00:23:09,320
it already exists.

208
00:23:11,967 --> 00:23:13,872
They are too noisy on rainy days.

209
00:23:48,317 --> 00:23:49,817
Grilling chicken with lychee wood.

210
00:23:50,120 --> 00:23:52,280
The chicken will have the aroma of lychee.

211
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:53,450
My bro said that

212
00:23:53,474 --> 00:23:56,270
the island owner's roast chicken can make
vegetarians break their abstinence.

213
00:23:59,645 --> 00:24:01,775
I can already imagine
how delicious it will be later.

214
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:02,825
It's in the pot.

215
00:24:11,160 --> 00:24:12,280
This fire is beautiful.

216
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:13,040
I told you so.

217
00:24:32,720 --> 00:24:34,080
No one gave me a seat.

218
00:24:34,080 --> 00:24:35,080
Nobody want to drink anymore?

219
00:24:35,247 --> 00:24:36,372
I don't want it.

220
00:24:36,440 --> 00:24:37,200
Here's a seat for you.

221
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:38,380
Leave it here.

222
00:24:40,920 --> 00:24:41,989
Be careful.

223
00:24:42,036 --> 00:24:43,591
Be careful.

224
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:45,528
Here you go.

225
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:48,645
Is there no bowls?

226
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:49,560
Here you go.

227
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:51,880
Coming!

228
00:24:52,120 --> 00:24:52,973
Here comes the roast chicken.

229
00:24:53,989 --> 00:24:55,080
I'm going to start.

230
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:56,825
Start!

231
00:24:59,965 --> 00:25:01,130
I want to eat chicken legs.

232
00:25:01,155 --> 00:25:02,320
You want to eat chicken legs?

233
00:25:02,345 --> 00:25:03,840
I want it, I want it too.

234
00:25:07,012 --> 00:25:08,760
You are smart, you are the smartest.

235
00:25:10,872 --> 00:25:11,958
You are the smartest.

236
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:55,000
I was so tired yesterday.

237
00:27:55,040 --> 00:27:56,240
I fell asleep as soon as
my head hit the pillow.

238
00:27:56,724 --> 00:27:58,724
I didn't even notice you weren't in the room.

239
00:28:01,640 --> 00:28:03,215
I had so much fun painting last night.

240
00:28:07,560 --> 00:28:08,800
Can you give me this painting?

241
00:28:19,491 --> 00:28:21,247
If I painted the walls red.

242
00:28:22,138 --> 00:28:23,538
And hang it up...

243
00:28:25,120 --> 00:28:26,560
It can be called Night Fire.

244
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:29,160
If the wall is painted blue,

245
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:32,520
it can be called Deep Sea.

246
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:37,920
You got it?

247
00:28:39,560 --> 00:28:40,800
Is that hard to understand?

248
00:28:46,320 --> 00:28:47,169
You can have it.

249
00:28:56,280 --> 00:28:58,080
I shouldn't define it though.

250
00:28:59,560 --> 00:29:01,520
Like the roast chicken last night.

251
00:29:01,707 --> 00:29:02,707
Put it there,

252
00:29:03,920 --> 00:29:04,920
and it's a stove.

253
00:29:28,107 --> 00:29:29,122
Wow.

254
00:29:39,560 --> 00:29:40,720
It's too high. We can't reach it.

255
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:43,400
Our dinner was too greasy last night.

256
00:29:44,360 --> 00:29:46,919
In fact, lemons can also relieve the greasiness.

257
00:29:47,276 --> 00:29:49,116
I just want to hit them.

258
00:30:10,245 --> 00:30:11,205
Try it, it's delicious.

259
00:31:18,040 --> 00:31:19,026
Xiaozhi.

260
00:31:39,320 --> 00:31:40,120
What's up?

261
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:41,160
I'm fine.

262
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:49,635
What you said the other day,

263
00:31:50,412 --> 00:31:51,652
I thought about it.

264
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:56,760
Everyone says that
whatever exists is reasonable.

265
00:31:58,960 --> 00:32:00,362
Then as you said,

266
00:32:00,902 --> 00:32:02,338
that's a false proposition.

267
00:32:08,760 --> 00:32:11,229
Xiaozhi, are you listening?

268
00:32:11,800 --> 00:32:13,000
Yeah.

269
00:32:24,857 --> 00:32:28,657
If existence needs to be explained
by whether it is reasonable or not,

270
00:32:30,268 --> 00:32:31,668
then it is not existence anymore.

271
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:34,620
Just like the birds outside the window.

272
00:32:35,680 --> 00:32:37,174
They chirp outside the window.

273
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:38,885
We hear their sounds in one way.

274
00:32:39,480 --> 00:32:41,960
But when they hear their own sounds,
it's another way.

275
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:47,120
However, their sounds never change
just because of who is listening.

276
00:33:44,920 --> 00:33:46,880
Xiao Long, there is not enough butter.

277
00:33:47,840 --> 00:33:48,854
I'll call the courier.

